# UI Stack Conventions

## Layout & Styling → Tailwind Only
Use Tailwind utility classes for ALL layout, spacing, typography, and color.
Never use MUI layout components: `Box`, `Stack`, `Grid`, `Container`, `Paper`, `Card`, `CardContent`, `Typography`, `Divider`, `AppBar`, `Toolbar`, `Drawer`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<Stack spacing={3}><Box sx={{ mt: 2 }}>...</Box></Stack>

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="flex flex-col gap-6"><div>...</div></div>
```

## MUI Allowed Components
Only use MUI for interactive form/feedback components:
- `TextField`, `Select`, `Autocomplete` — form inputs
- `Button` — inside forms/dialogs only
- `Dialog`, `DialogTitle`, `DialogContent`, `DialogActions`
- `Chip` — tags, badges, labels
- `Snackbar` / `useSnackbar` from notistack

## Spacing Rule: Gap Over Margin
**Never** apply `margin` or `padding` to child components.
Use `gap-*` on flex/grid parents. Apply `py-*/px-*` only on the section/container itself.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — padding/margin on children
<div><p className="mt-4">text</p><p className="mt-2">text</p></div>

// ✅ GOOD — gap on parent
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4"><p>text</p><p>text</p></div>
```

## Section Wrapper Pattern
```tsx
<section className="bg-background-secondary py-20 md:py-28">
  <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 flex flex-col gap-10">
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</section>
```

## Animations
Define keyframes in `<style jsx global>` or `globals.css`.
Apply via className strings (`.hero-title`, `.hero-badge`, etc.).
